Were you all (meaning the aforementioned inbred hicks) under the impression that plantation owners and slave traders regularly gave slaves chocolate and bubble baths? That slaves were justly compensated with monetary wage and reasonable working conditions?

Slaves were considered property. Like Calvin Candie says, "Broomhilda is my property, and I can choose to do with my property whatever I desire." This was the dominant understanding of slave code throughout the lands in which slavery was legal, and this is why, as Gunslinger5001 feels the need to cry about, "all the white people are evil slave owning county folk who rape black women." It doesn't matter what color they are: Anyone that feels they have ownership of a human life is evil and those people did to their property whatever they desired, which included rape, even though there was no rape in this movie that I can remember.

Most importantly, though, is the fact that the other fucking main protagonist is white (and German) and the final fucking antagonist is a black slave, which completely shatters this entire "anti-white" arguments the inbreds like to circle jerk over.
